The National Security Advisors of the United States, Japan, and the Republic of Korea have congratulated the University of Tokyo, Seoul National University, and the University of Chicago for signing a trilateral quantum partnership. This partnership aims to train a quantum workforce and enhance competitiveness in the global economy. The signing of this agreement is seen as a step towards fulfilling the commitment made by the leaders of the three countries to demonstrate the benefits of trilateral cooperation. In addition, this partnership follows the signing of a Trilateral Framework in December to encourage scientific cooperation among national laboratories. The United States, Japan, and the Republic of Korea are leaders in research and development investment, and partnerships like this one enable them to capitalize on the advancements in scientific research and technology to drive new industries and modernize existing ones. The National Security Advisors express their best wishes for the success of these universities in their quantum endeavors.